# Computexchange — environment for both binaries.
# Copy to `.env` and fill in. The Makefile loads `.env` if present, so
# DATABASE_URL (and friends) flow into `make migrate` / `make control` /
# `make e2e` without re-typing. Defaults below match docker-compose.yml
# (Postgres + MinIO), so the dev stack works out of the box.
#
# There is NO silent auth bypass. The buyer api_key and the worker_token are
# MINTED by the control plane's seed step (`make seed` → `cd control && go run .
# seed`), which inserts a hashed api_key into `api_keys` and a token into
# `worker_tokens` and prints both to stdout. Copy the printed worker_token into
# CX_WORKER_TOKEN below; pass the printed api_key as the job-submit Bearer token.

# ── Control plane (Go) ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Postgres DSN. user/pass/db must match POSTGRES_* in docker-compose.yml.
DATABASE_URL=postgres://cx:cx@localhost:5432/cx?sslmode=disable
# Address the REST API + worker protocol listen on (host:port). LISTEN_ADDR is
# the canonical name; CONTROL_PLANE_ADDR is accepted as an alias. Default :8080.
LISTEN_ADDR=:8080
# Canonical public HTTPS origin used to bind cxer2 enrollment approvals. Required
# for every non-loopback deployment, including direct TLS and reverse proxies;
# the server intentionally trusts neither Host nor X-Forwarded-Proto for it.
# No path, query, fragment, credentials, or trailing slash.
# CX_PUBLIC_CONTROL_ORIGIN=https://control.example.com
# S3-compatible object storage (MinIO in dev). S3_ENDPOINT is how the CONTROL
# PLANE reaches the store (internal: PutObject/GetObject). S3_PUBLIC_ENDPOINT is
# the host that PRESIGNED URLs are signed against — the address the AGENT uses to
# GET inputs / PUT results. In single-host dev both are localhost:9000; under the
# full compose stack the control plane reaches minio at http://minio:9000 while
# presigns are signed against http://localhost:9000 (see docker-compose.yml).
S3_ENDPOINT=http://localhost:9000
S3_PUBLIC_ENDPOINT=http://localhost:9000
S3_BUCKET=cx-jobs
S3_ACCESS_KEY=minioadmin
S3_SECRET_KEY=minioadmin
S3_REGION=us-east-1

# ── Supplier agent (Rust) ────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Where the agent reaches the control plane (no trailing slash).
CX_CONTROL_URL=http://localhost:8080
# Per-worker auth token. Set this to the worker_token PRINTED BY `make seed`. It
# must exist as a row in worker_tokens (token, worker_id, supplier_id,
# revoked=false) or registration/poll/commit are rejected.
CX_WORKER_TOKEN=replace-me-with-seed-worker-token
# Optional: override the HuggingFace model cache directory (defaults to
# ~/.cache/huggingface). Models are downloaded once on first use and never
# re-fetched or deleted (a model pulled yesterday still resolves today).
# CX_MODEL_CACHE=/path/to/model/cache
# Installed macOS app launches set this automatically. Direct production agent
# launchers should also require containment; development remains warning-only.
# CX_REQUIRE_SANDBOX=1

# Optional owned Candle speculative decode. Off by default until the batched
# verifier/fleet soak is promoted. `ngram` enables lossless prompt-lookup drafts;
# every proposed token is checked by the real target model before commit. Exact-
# length multi-row jobs use bounded synchronized cohorts (B<=4); singleton/ragged
# rows retain the exact single-stream loop. This remains workload-gated: measured
# high-copy batches win, while low-yield batches can trail batched greedy.
# CX_SPEC_DECODE=ngram
# CX_SPEC_DECODE_WINDOW=4       # 1..32; four is the current measured Metal bucket
# CX_SPEC_DECODE_NGRAM_ORDER=3  # 1..64
# Optional Q4_K Metal verifier kernels; both are off by default. Skinny-M takes
# priority for eligible M=2..5 calls; split-K remains its independent fallback.
# CX_Q4K_SKINNY_M=1
# CX_Q4K_SPLITK=1

# Local-only render speculation preview (`cx-agent spec-render-preview --input ...`).
# This command never registers, polls, commits, bills, or contacts control. Every
# executable/controller component is operator-selected and content-addressed; use
# absolute paths and compute each digest after every intentional edit.
# CX_SPEC_RENDER_PREVIEW_DRIVER=/absolute/path/to/scripts/spec-lab/cx_agent_render_preview_driver.py
# CX_SPEC_RENDER_PREVIEW_DRIVER_SHA256=64-lowercase-hex
# CX_SPEC_RENDER_PREVIEW_BACKEND=/absolute/path/to/operator-render-backend.py
# CX_SPEC_RENDER_PREVIEW_BACKEND_SHA256=64-lowercase-hex
# CX_SPEC_RENDER_PREVIEW_CORE_SHA256=64-lowercase-hex
# CX_SPEC_RENDER_PREVIEW_ADAPTER_SHA256=64-lowercase-hex
# CX_SPEC_RENDER_PREVIEW_TIMEOUT_SECS=120  # 1..3600
# First-party real Cycles backend (still local preview-only):
# CX_SPEC_RENDER_PREVIEW_BACKEND=/absolute/path/to/scripts/spec-lab/cx_cycles_render_preview_backend.py
# CX_SPEC_RENDER_CYCLES_BLENDER=/Applications/Blender.app/Contents/MacOS/Blender
# CX_SPEC_RENDER_CYCLES_BLENDER_SHA256=64-lowercase-hex
# CX_SPEC_RENDER_CYCLES_SCENE_ROOT=/absolute/operator-owned/scenes
# CX_SPEC_RENDER_CYCLES_OUTPUT_ROOT=/absolute/operator-owned/preview-output
# CX_SPEC_RENDER_CYCLES_TIMEOUT_SECS=120  # 1..600 per render

# ── Payments + payouts (Stripe) ──────────────────────────────────────────────
# The control plane's SECRET key only (sk_test_… in test mode, sk_live_… live).
# Powers buyer charges AND supplier payouts (Connect transfers). Server-side ONLY
# — never the publishable key, never in client code, never committed.
# STRIPE_SECRET_KEY=sk_test_xxx
# Webhook signing secret (whsec_…) from the endpoint you point at /v1/stripe/webhook.
# Verifies saved-card, successful-collection reconciliation, refund, and dispute
# events. `scripts/stripe-webhooks.sh` installs the exact required event set.
# STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET=whsec_xxx
# Separate signing secret for the endpoint at /v1/stripe/connect-webhook.
# Production requires a distinct value because Stripe signs each endpoint with its
# own secret. `scripts/stripe-webhooks.sh` can create both endpoints and write both
# values without printing them.
# CX_CONNECT_WEBHOOK_SECRET=whsec_xxx
# Required in production. Both must be HTTPS URLs on SITE_HOST; startup refuses
# missing, cross-origin, credential-bearing, or non-standard-port values.
# CX_CONNECT_RETURN_URL=https://computexchange.net/earn?connected=1
# CX_CONNECT_REFRESH_URL=https://computexchange.net/earn/connect/refresh
#
# The PUBLISHABLE key (pk_…) is NOT set here — it is a front-end value (Stripe.js
# in the browser), safe to expose in the web-app config. The control plane never
# needs it.

# ── GitHub connect (Concierge intake) ────────────────────────────────────────
# A GitHub OAuth App's credentials. Its callback URL must be
# /v1/connect/github/callback. Without these, connect is an honest 503, never faked.
# GITHUB_CLIENT_ID=xxx
# GITHUB_CLIENT_SECRET=xxx
# GITHUB_REDIRECT_URL=https://<your-host>/v1/connect/github/callback

# ── Hardening (set once real tokens flow) ────────────────────────────────────
# At least 32 unpredictable bytes → AES-256-GCM-encrypts stored GitHub tokens and
# each customer webhook's independent signing secret at rest. OAuth tokens retain
# an explicit `plain:` dev fallback; production/live-money startup refuses an
# unset or short key and webhook registration fails closed without it.
# CX_TOKEN_KEY=replace-with-a-long-random-string
# OAuth state is generated randomly, stored hash-only, single-use, expiry-bound,
# and bound to a SameSite cookie. No reusable OAuth-state secret is configured.
# At least 32 unpredictable bytes, independent of CX_TOKEN_KEY, HMAC-selects audits.
# REQUIRED in production/live-money mode; never expose it to workers or clients.
# CX_VERIFICATION_SAMPLE_SECRET=replace-with-a-different-long-random-string

# Versioned quote/submit margin model. These deliberately have no runtime
# defaults: set values reviewed against the processor contract and CX operating
# costs. Percentage values are basis points (350 = 3.50%). The illustrative
# values below are placeholders, not a statement of Stripe's current pricing.
# CX_ECON_SCHEDULE_VERSION=operator-reviewed-YYYY-MM
# CX_PROCESSOR_PERCENT_BPS=350
# CX_PROCESSOR_FIXED_USD=0.35
# CX_CONTROL_PLANE_PER_TASK_USD=0.005
# CX_TARGET_MARGIN_BPS=300

# ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#  PRODUCTION OPS (docker-compose.prod.yml). The vars below are NOT needed for
#  local dev. They are what the OWNER fills in to run prod: the public stack,
#  offsite backups, and monitoring/alerting. See docs/RUNBOOKS.md.
# ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# ── Prod stack secrets (docker-compose.prod.yml) ─────────────────────────────
# Strong, generated values · NEVER the cx/cx + minioadmin dev defaults. Generate
# with e.g. `openssl rand -base64 32`.
# POSTGRES_PASSWORD=generate-a-strong-password
# MINIO_ROOT_USER=cxminio
# MINIO_ROOT_PASSWORD=generate-a-strong-password

# ── Public edge (Caddy) ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Email Let's Encrypt uses for the ACME account (expiry notices). REQUIRED · the
# caddy service refuses to start without it.
# ACME_EMAIL=ops@yourdomain
# The public hostnames Caddy serves + auto-certs. Defaults are the repo's
# computexchange.net / storage.computexchange.net; override for your domain.
# SITE_HOST=computexchange.net
# STORAGE_HOST=storage.computexchange.net

# ── Offsite backups / DR (scripts/backup.sh, scripts/restore.sh) ─────────────
# The OFFSITE S3-compatible destination for pg_dump + object-store backups. This
# is the WHOLE POINT of a backup · backup.sh exits nonzero if it is unset (it
# refuses to take a backup with nowhere offsite to put it). AWS S3 / DO Spaces /
# Cloudflare R2 / Backblaze B2 all work.
# CX_BACKUP_OFFSITE=s3://cx-backups/prod
# For non-AWS providers, the S3 API endpoint (leave unset for real AWS):
#   Spaces:  https://nyc3.digitaloceanspaces.com
#   R2:      https://<accountid>.r2.cloudflarestorage.com
#   B2:      https://s3.us-west-002.backblazeb2.com
# CX_BACKUP_S3_ENDPOINT=https://nyc3.digitaloceanspaces.com
# Credentials for the OFFSITE bucket (DISTINCT from the MinIO root creds above).
# The aws CLI reads these standard names; backup.sh fails loudly if unset.
# AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID=offsite-bucket-access-key
# AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY=offsite-bucket-secret-key
# AWS_DEFAULT_REGION=us-east-1
# How many local staging copies to keep under .artifacts/backups (offsite is the
# retained copy). Default 7.
# CX_BACKUP_KEEP_LOCAL=7

# ── Monitoring / alerting (--profile monitoring) ─────────────────────────────
# Grafana admin password (the grafana service refuses to start without it).
# GRAFANA_ADMIN_PASSWORD=generate-a-strong-password
# Alertmanager delivery. Unset = Alertmanager logs a loud delivery error on the
# first alert (never a silent drop), so set at least one real channel for prod.
# Slack incoming-webhook URL (all alerts):
# SLACK_WEBHOOK_URL=https://hooks.slack.com/services/T000/B000/xxxx
# PagerDuty Events v2 routing key (severity:page alerts):
# PAGERDUTY_ROUTING_KEY=your-pagerduty-routing-key
# Dead-man's-switch ping URL (e.g. healthchecks.io / Dead Man's Snitch). The
# always-firing heartbeat posts here; the watchdog pages YOU if it ever stops.
# DEADMANSSWITCH_URL=https://hc-ping.com/your-uuid
